objects.name: speccom
objects.description: SpecCom is a malicious 32-bit Windows executable for Windows (x86 PE) that communicates with command and control (C2) infrastructure over HTTP using the Windows WinInet API. Tasking is delivered within HTML comment tags and is Base64-encoded with multiple layers of XOR obfuscation using hard-coded keys (a 'malware key' and a 'traffic key'), with string-specific XOR keys derived from the first bytes of the obfuscated strings. The analyzed sample supports uploading data and executing Windows command-prompt commands as new processes, sending periodic tasking requests to hard-coded URL paths (e.g., /gin/kw.asp) and posting output to corresponding paths (e.g., /gin/tab.asp). Configuration strings (including C2 domain, XOR key, and URL paths) are XOR-obfuscated, and strings used in functionality are dynamically built on the stack to evade detection. The malware launches its main functionality from a window procedure for a window named 'Help and Support' to avoid heuristic detection and uses additional GUI-related APIs. This report lists extensive C2 domains and URL paths used by various samples, and provides YARA rules detecting distinctive SpecCom artifacts. The NCSC assesses SpecCom as relatively low-sophistication malware.

objects.name: SpecCom_get_mac_address
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule SpecCom_get_mac_address {
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Detects SpecCom obtaining MAC address"

    strings:
        $ = {8D 8D F0 80 FF FF 51 8D 8D FC 80 FF FF 51 C7 85 F0 80 FF FF
90 7E 00 00 FF D0 8B C8 33 C0 C6 45 F4 00 8D 7D F5 AB 66 AB AA 85 C9 0F
85 1D 01 00 00 53 6A 25 5E 6A 30 5A 6A 32 59 8B C6 66 89 45 8C 8B C2 66
89 45 8E 6A 58 8B C1 66 89 45 90}
        $ = {8D 8D 00 81 FF FF 51 8D 95 04 81 FF FF 52 C7 85 00 81 FF FF
90 7E 00 00 FF D0 85 C0 0F 85 C7 00 00 00 8B 85 9C 82 FF FF 8B C8 C1 E9
08 0F B6 D1 52 0F B6 C0 50 8B 85 98 82 FF FF 8B C8 C1 E9 18 51 8B D0 C1
EA 10 0F B6 CA 51 8B D0 C1 EA 08 0F B6 CA 0F B6 D0 51 52 8D 45 94}
    condition:
        (uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and uint16(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x4550) and any
of them
}
